===Noun===
'''fuil''' ''m'' ([[genitive|gen.]] [[fola]]; [[plural|pl.]] [[fola]])
#[[blood]]

[[Category:Irish nouns]]

===Verb===
[[Dependent]] form of the [[present]] [[indicative]] of [[bí]] 'to [[be]]'

Examples of use (with interrogative particle [[an#Irish|an]]):
:'''an bhfuil [[mé]]''' or '''an [[fuilim|bhfuilim]]''' &mdash; '[[am]] [[I]]?'
:'''an bhfuil [[tú]]''' — '[[are]] [[you]] ([[singular|sg.]])?'
:'''an bhfuil [[sé]]''' — '[[is]] [[he]]?'
:'''an bhfuil [[sí]]''' — '[[is]] [[she]]?'
:'''an bhfuil [[muid]]''' or '''an [[fuilimid|bhfuilimid]]''' &mdash; '[[are]] [[we]]?'
:'''an bhfuil [[sibh]]''' — '[[are]] [[you]] ([[plural|pl.]])?'
:'''an bhfuil [[siad]]''' — '[[are]] [[they]]?'

Also used in shortened form in the negative: (shortened from [[ní]] fhuil to níl)
:'''níl [[mé]]''' or '''nílim''' &mdash; I am not
:'''níl [[tú]]''' — [[you]] [[are]] [[not]]
:'''níl [[sé]]''' — [[he]] [[is]] [[not]]
:'''níl [[sí]]''' — [[she]] [[is]] [[not]]
:'''níl [[muid]]''' or '''níl [[sinn]]''' or '''[[nílimid]]''' &mdash; [[we]] [[are]] [[not]]
:'''níl [[sibh]]''' — [[you]] ([[plural|pl.]]) [[are]] [[not]]
:'''níl [[siad]]''' — [[they]] [[are]] [[not]]

